    "type": "spell",
    "data": {
        "description": {
            "value": "<p>You try to turn the target's flesh into stone. The target must attempt a Fortitude save.</p>\n<p><strong>Critical Success</strong> The target is unaffected.</p>\n<p><strong>Success</strong> The target is @Compendium[pf2e.conditionspf2e.xYTAsEpcJE1Ccni3]{Slowed} 1 for 1 round.</p>\n<p><strong>Failure</strong> The target is @Compendium[pf2e.conditionspf2e.xYTAsEpcJE1Ccni3]{Slowed} 1 and must attempt a Fortitude save at the end of each of its turns; this ongoing save has the incapacitation trait. On a failed save, the @Compendium[pf2e.conditionspf2e.xYTAsEpcJE1Ccni3]{Slowed} condition increases by 1 (or 2 on a critical failure). A successful save reduces the @Compendium[pf2e.conditionspf2e.xYTAsEpcJE1Ccni3]{Slowed} condition by 1. When a creature is unable to act due to the @Compendium[pf2e.conditionspf2e.xYTAsEpcJE1Ccni3]{Slowed} condition from flesh to stone, the creature is @Compendium[pf2e.conditionspf2e.dTwPJuKgBQCMxixg]{Petrified} permanently. The spell ends if the creature is @Compendium[pf2e.conditionspf2e.dTwPJuKgBQCMxixg]{Petrified} or the @Compendium[pf2e.conditionspf2e.xYTAsEpcJE1Ccni3]{Slowed} condition is removed.</p>\n<p><strong>Critical Failure</strong> As failure, but the target is initially @Compendium[pf2e.conditionspf2e.xYTAsEpcJE1Ccni3]{Slowed} 2.</p>",
